channel.title: Need help with running server (508)
channel.description:
Okay, when i run my server this comes up....... :eek:
Exception in thread "main" jave.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: palidino76/rs2/server Caused by: java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: palidino76.rs2.server at java.net.URLClassloader$1.run at java.security.AccessController.doPrivileged at java.net.URLClassloader.findClass at java.lang.ClassLoader.loadClass at sun.misc.Launcher$AppClassLoader.loadClass at java.lang.ClassLoader.loadClass at java.lang.ClassLoader.loadClassInternal Press any key to continue . . .
:confused: :eek: So if someone could tell me whats wrong that would be great, please help! I've owned servers that have had some problems but none that have done this so idk what to do...... i'm in some big need of help, i wouldn't have come to mopar if i new what was wrong. So if anyone had same problem post your reply on how you fixed. Also every run file i use it says......... "The system cannot not find the path specified." :confused: So that could use some help too. well i'll keep checking this post untell i get a reply that works. :( Thank you for your time, your friend Sean.
